<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 03 at 7:26PM CDT  by NWS Midland-Odessa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of far northwestern
Ector, southwestern Andrews and northeastern Winkler Counties
through 815 PM CDT...
At 725 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Andrews, moving southwest at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Rural areas of southwest Andrews.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
